YAWL Version 6.0.0-Beta
=======================

Release Date: February 25, 2026
Release Type: Beta (Pre-Release)

Contributors:
- Sean Chatman (Library Modernization Lead & Architecture Consultant)
- Claude Code Agent Team, Anthropic (AI-Assisted Development & Code Quality Automation)

Original Authors:
- YAWL Foundation Team

Description:
This beta release builds on the v6.0.0-Alpha foundation with documentation consolidation,
version alignment across all 14 modules, and continued quality improvements toward
production readiness.

Major Changes:
- Version bump from Alpha to Beta across entire codebase
- Documentation consolidation (185 files archived, 46 canonical docs in docs/v6/)
- 77% of violations resolved (47/61)
- All BLOCKER violations resolved (12/12)
- Java 25 modernization complete (226+ switch expressions, 275+ pattern matches)
- MCP and A2A integration operational

Status: Beta Release
- Feature-complete for core functionality
- Suitable for integration testing and evaluation
- Not recommended for production use
- Feedback welcome via GitHub issues

Next Steps:
- Release candidate (RC1) for full violation resolution
- Production validation and SOC 2 compliance
- Stable 6.0.0 release

For detailed changes, see CHANGELOG.md
For technical details, see docs/v6/

